Lets take a break for tonight. Before that just tell me how are we going to build this project and what is the end goal of this project. 

Cool. Here’s the plan and the end goal — clean, concrete, no fantasy.

End goal

A Secure Research Artifact Registry backend that you can put on your resume as a “real” system:

Users can log in (JWT)

Users can create artifacts (models / datasets / experiments / papers)

Artifacts support versions

Artifacts can be private / shared / public

Users can upload files tied to a version

Access is enforced with permissions, not vibes

Everything has clean API design: filtering, pagination, proper status codes

Later add deployment (Docker/CI/CD) when the core is solid

Think: “private HuggingFace-lite” for research outputs.

This is a strong SDE project because it proves you can build backend systems with security + data modeling.

#########################################################################################

How we’re going to build it (phases)
Phase 1 — Foundation (already mostly done)

Register/login ✅

Password hashing ✅

JWT issuance ✅

Token verification + protected route ✅ (/auth/me)

Swagger auth works ✅

Deliverable: auth is real and reusable.


######################################################################################################


Phase 2 — Core domain: Artifacts + versions

We add models:

Artifact (owner, title, type, visibility, description, created_at)

ArtifactVersion (artifact_id, version tag, changelog, created_at)

Endpoints:

POST /artifacts (create)

GET /artifacts (list mine + shared with me)

GET /artifacts/{id} (permission check)

POST /artifacts/{id}/versions

GET /artifacts/{id}/versions

Deliverable: usable registry without files.



################################################################################################################





Phase 3 — Sharing & permissions

Add model:

AccessGrant (artifact_id, user_id, role: viewer/editor)

Rules:

PRIVATE: only owner

SHARED: owner + grants

PUBLIC: anyone can view metadata

Deliverable: security story becomes legit.

######################################################################################################

Phase 4 — File upload

Add:

ArtifactFile metadata (file_id, version_id, filename, size, checksum)

store file bytes on disk (./storage/) for MVP

Endpoints:

upload/download with permission checks

Deliverable: registry stores real artifacts, not just text.


#########################################################################################################

Phase 5 — Resume-ready polish

Pagination + filters

Error handling consistency

Logging (no sensitive data)

Basic audit log (who created/updated/downloaded)

######################################################################################################

Then (later):

Postgres migration

Docker + deploy

CI/CD tests

The “so what” for interviews

You’ll be able to talk about:

stateless auth and tradeoffs

RBAC/ownership enforcement

relational modeling & constraints

safe file handling

API design decisions

That’s the point. Not the app itself.